    {
      "text": "Symmetric inflammatory polyarthritis involving bilateral MCPs, PIPs, wrists, and MTPs with morning stiffness >1 hour. Strongly positive RF (78 IU/mL) and anti-CCP (>250 U/mL) with elevated inflammatory markers (ESR 42, CRP 2.8). High clinical suspicion for rheumatoid arthritis. Urgent referral to rheumatology placed."
